{"id": "duc04-testb-1:12#36", "contents": "Granik mentioned that refunds to fans would be made at the end of the calendar month, with the first refund including monies for canceled preseason games. He estimated the losses to be in the \"hundreds of millions of dollars.\" Granik expressed concerns about the tax system's ability to address the economic needs of the situation, but acknowledged the possibility of exploring this option. Stern shared similar sentiments, stating that the league owes it to the fans to revisit the notion of a tax rate that could potentially achieve the desired result. However, he noted that the outlook is not promising, and the next two days would be spent exploring this possibility."}
